{
  "text": "One of the rarest forms of esophageal perforation is Boerhaave syndrome (BS). It is a spontaneous rupture of the esophagus caused by impaired coordination of the act of vomiting and attempts to stop it. Various scientific reports estimate it at 8-25% [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
